<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0333">
<l>maṉṉuñ ciṉṉu māṉu mīṉum</l>
<l>piṉṉu muṉṉu viṉaiyeñcu kiḷaviyu</l>
<l>maṉṉa viyala veṉmaṉār pulavar</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Scholars say that <foreign xml:lang="ta">maṉ, ciṉ, āṉ, īṉ, piṉ, muṉ</foreign></l>
<l>and the adverbial participle behave in the same manner.<note place="foot">The adverbial participle referred to is the one which ends in <foreign xml:lang="ta">-iṉ,</foreign> e.g. <foreign xml:lang="ta">variṉ + kollum &gt; varirkollum.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
